{
  "texts": [
    "The absence of a uniform classification system, which results in inconsistent waste sorting processes, is another key problem (Edjabou et al. 2015).",
    "This makes it more difficult to recycle and recover resources effectively.",
    "Furthermore, the growth of complicated and composite materials poses a significant obstacle.",
    "These materials frequently challenge traditional classification models, necessitating new models to guarantee accurate classification.",
    "Additionally, improper classification and separation of hazardous materials pose serious environmental and public health risks (Ahmed et al. 2023a)."
  ]
}